ixed X11 public-domain core bitmap fonts have provided substantial Unicode coverage since 1997.\n|-\n|Fixedsys Excelsior ||[[public domain]] ||3.01 / 2007 ||\n|-\n|[[Gentium]] ||[[SIL Open Font License|OFL]] or [[BSD licenses|BSD-like license]] ||5.000 (2014-10-28)\n|-\n|[[Ghostscript]]\n|[[GNU General Public License|GPL]], [[Aladdin Free Public License|AFPL]], [[LaTeX Project Public License|LPPL]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Ghostscript SVN - URW fonts |work=Google Code |publisher=Google |url=http://code.google.com/p/ghostscript/source/browse/#svn/trunk/urw-fonts |accessdate=2010-04-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Debian package - gsfonts |work=packages.debian.org |publisher=Debian |url=http://packages.debian.org/sid/gsfonts |accessdate=2010-04-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Fonts and font facilities supplied with Ghostscript |publisher=Ghostscript |url=http://www.ghostscript.com/doc/current/Fonts.htm |accessdate=2010-04-21}}</ref><ref>{{citation |title=URW++ making original 35 fonts available under LPPL |publisher=tug.org |url=http://www.tug.org/fonts/lppl-urw.txt |accessdate=2010-05-06}}</ref><ref>{{Citation |title=Finally! Good-quality free (GPL) basic-35 PostScript Type 1 fonts. |url=http://www.geocrawler.com/archives/3/378/1996/5/0/2064811/ |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20021023155414/http://www.geocrawler.com/archives/3/378/1996/5/0/2064811/ |archivedate=2002-10-23 |accessdate=2010-05-06}}</ref><ref>{{Citation |title=Finally! Good-quality free (GPL) basic-35 PostScript Type 1 fonts. |format=TXT |publisher=tug.org |url=http://www.tug.org/fonts/deutsch-urw.txt |accessdate=2010-05-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Fonts and TeX |url=http://www.tug.org/fonts/ |date=2009-12-19 |accessdate=2010-05-06}}</ref><ref>{{citation |title=Five years after: Report on international TEX font projects |format=PDF |publisher=tug.org |year=2007 |url=http://www.tug.org/TUGboat/Articles/tb29-1/tb91ludwichowski-fonts.pdf |accessdate=2010-05-06}}</ref>\n|\n|URW ++ Type 1 fonts, a free alternatives to 35 [[PostScript fonts#Core Font Set|basic PostScript fonts]]\u2014e.g. Type 1 version of [[Nimbus Roman No9 L]], [[Nimbus Sans L]], [[Nimbus Mono L]], URW Bookman L, URW Gothic L and others\n|-\n|[[GNU Unifont]] ||GPL 2+ ||13.0.01 (28 March 2020)\n| GNU Unifont is a bitmap-based font created by Roman Czyborra that is present in most free operating systems.\n|-\n|[http://fonts.jp/hanazono/ Hanazono Minch\u014d]<sup>&#x5b;in Japanese&#x5d;</sup>\n|(permissive license)\n|\n|One of the few free software fonts that includes the whole [[CJK Unified Ideographs#CJK Unified Ideographs Extension C|CJK Unified Ideographs Extension C]] block, as well as many other (related) [[CJKV]] characters, such as the Kangxi Radicals and CJK Radicals Supplement blocks.\n|-\n|[[IBM Plex]]||[[SIL Open Font License|OFL]] || 2.0 / Jun 5, 2019 ||IBM Plex is designed and developed by Mike Abbink at IBM in collaboration with Bold Monday, it is the replacement of Helvetica as the corporate typeface.\n|-\n|[[Jomolhari (typeface)|Jomolhari]] ||[[SIL Open Font License|OFL]] || ||Tibetan script\n|-\n|[[Junicode]] ||[[GNU General Public License|GPL]] ||1.002 / 25 June 2018\n|-\n|[http://www.deviantart.com/art/Kelvinch-Release-Version-600800030 Kelvinch Font]\n|[[SIL Open Font License|OFL]], free for any use\n|\n|Most Latin blocks fully populated + Cyrillic, Georgian, Armenian & Runes. Comes in Roman, Italic, Bold & Bold Italic.\n|-\n|[[Computer Modern#Latin Modern|Latin Modern]] ||[http://www.gust.org.pl/projects/e-foundry/licenses GUST licence] || || Another derivative of Computer Modern\n|-\n|[[Lato (typeface)|Lato]] || [[SIL Open Font License|OFL]] || 2.015 / 6 August 2015 || Covers all Latin alphabets, along with Cyrillic, Greek, and IPA\n|-\n|[[Linux Libertine]] ||[[GNU General Public License|GPL]], [[SIL Open Font License|OFL]] ||5.3.0 / July 2012 || Linux Libertine is a digital typeface created by the Libertine Open Fonts Project, which aims to create free and open altern