{"title_page": "Laila El Garaa", "text_new": "{{short description|Moroccan Paralympic athlete}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n| image           = Laila El Garaa F40 Discus London.jpg\n| alt             = \n| birth_name      = \n| native_name     = \n| native_lang     = \n| other_names     =\n| birth_date      = \n| birth_place     = \n| residence       = \n| height          = \n| weight          = \n| club            = \n| coach           =\n| disability_class= [[T40 (classification)|F40]]\n| years_active    = 2006\u20132012 ([[Track and field]] F40)\n| medaltemplates  =\n{{MedalSport|Women's [[para athletics]]}}\n{{MedalCountry|{{MAR}}}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Paralympic Games]]}}\n{{MedalSilver| [[2004 Summer Paralympics|2004 Athens]] | [[Athletics at the 2004 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Women's shot putt F40|Shot Putt \u2013 F40]]}}\n{{MedalBronze| [[2008 Summer Paralympics|2008 Beijing]] | [[Athletics at the 2008 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Women's shot put F40|Shot Putt - F40]]}}\n}}\n\n'''Laila El Garaa''' (Arabic: \u0644\u064a\u0644\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u06ad\u0631\u0639\u0629) is a [[Paralympian]] [[Track and field|athlete]] from [[Morocco]] competing mainly in category F40 shot putt events.\n\nShe competed in the [[2004 Summer Paralympics]] in [[Athens]], [[Greece]]. There she won a silver medal in the women's F40 shot putt event.  She also took part in the women's F40 javelin throw\n\nShe also competed in the [[2008 Summer Paralympics]] in [[Beijing]], [[People's Republic of China|China]]. There she won a bronze medal in the women's F40 shot putt event.  She also took part in the women's F40 discus throw.\n\n==External links==\n* {{IPC athlete|id=laila-el-garaa|old_id=688307}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Garaa, Laila El}}\n[[Category:Paralympic athletes of Morocco]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2004 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2008 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2012 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Paralympic silver medalists for Morocco]]\n[[Category:Paralympic bronze medalists for Morocco]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2004 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2008 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Moroccan female discus throwers]]\n[[Category:Moroccan female shot putters]]\n[[Category:Competitors in athletics with dwarfism]]\n[[Category:Female competitors in athletics with disabilities]]\n\n\n{{Morocco-athletics-bio-stub}}\n{{Paralympic-medalist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Moroccan Paralympic athlete}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n| image           = Laila El Garaa F40 Discus London.jpg\n| alt             = \n| birth_name      = \n| native_name     = \n| native_lang     = \n| other_names     =\n| birth_date      = \n| birth_place     = \n| residence       = \n| height          = \n| weight          = \n| club            = \n| coach           =\n| disability_class= [[T40 (classification)|F40]]\n| years_active    = 2006\u20132012 ([[Track and field]] F40)\n| medaltemplates  =\n{{MedalSport|Women's [[para athletics]]}}\n{{MedalCountry|{{MAR}}}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Paralympic Games]]}}\n{{MedalSilver| [[2004 Summer Paralympics|2004 Athens]] | [[Athletics at the 2004 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Women's shot putt F40|Shot Putt \u2013 F40]]}}\n{{MedalBronze| [[2008 Summer Paralympics|2008 Beijing]] | [[Athletics at the 2008 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Women's shot put F40|Shot Putt - F40]]}}\n}}\n\n'''Laila El Garaa''' (Arabic: \u0644\u064a\u0644\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u06ad\u0631\u0639\u0629) is a [[Paralympian]] [[Track and field|athlete]] from [[Morocco]] competing mainly in category F40 shot putt events.\n\nShe competed in the [[2004 Summer Paralympics]] in [[Athens]], [[Greece]]. There she won a silver medal in the women's F40 shot putt event.  She also took part in the women's F40 javelin throw\n\nShe also competed in the [[2008 Summer Paralympics]] in [[Beijing]], [[People's Republic of China|China]]. There she won a bronze medal in the women's F40 shot putt event.  She also took part in the women's F40 discus throw.\n\n==External links==\n* {{IPC athlete|688307}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Garaa, Laila El}}\n[[Category:Paralympic athletes of Morocco]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2004 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2008 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2012 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Paralympic silver medalists for Morocco]]\n[[Category:Paralympic bronze medalists for Morocco]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2004 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2008 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Moroccan female discus throwers]]\n[[Category:Moroccan female shot putters]]\n[[Category:Competitors in athletics with dwarfism]]\n[[Category:Female competitors in athletics with disabilities]]\n\n\n{{Morocco-athletics-bio-stub}}\n{{Paralympic-medalist-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Zyxw", "label": "safe", "comment": "update IPC external link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laila_El_Garaa"}
